My songs are missing from folders/library.\nA. Please ensure you have all your folders with music actually checked in Poweramp Settings => Folders and Library => Music Folders.\nYour original Android Library is not changed, nor any files deleted.\n\nPoweramp library is a separate, completely independent library. When you installed Poweramp 2.0, it just got filled with the files scanned from your sd card/other flash memory, as specified in Music Folders. \n\nQ. Freeze/too slow folders/library scan\nA. You have (semi)broken SD card. Please check your SD card for errors on computer or try another SD card.\n\nQ. Volume too low.  Volume changes weirdly. Other volume issues.\nA. Try to disable Direct Volume Control in Poweramp Settings => Audio => Advanced Tweaks.\n\nPoweramp 2.x uses Direct Volume Control by default on 2.3+ mid-to-high end devices. On stock ROMs this produces much better audio output. But many custom/buggy ROMs, while supporting DVC, can fail with it.\n\nQ. Poweramp 2.0 widget becomes white/doesn\'t work on phone reboot\nA. This can happen if something blocks Poweramp from starting on reboot and updating the widget - task managers, auto-start tweaking. If you use such apps/tweaks, you may need to add Poweramp (or/and WidgetPack) to exceptions list. \n\nQ. Can I get Poweramp v1.4 look?\nA. You can download \"Poweramp Classic Skin\" on Market."

    description: "DaTuner (Lite) is an all-purpose, precise and responsive chromatic tuner app for android with a simple interface.\n\nDaTuner Pro was recently reviewed by Android Central:\n\n\"For the Android-loving musician, I think DaTuner Pro is easily the best tuner you can have on your device. I used to give that title to *see review!*, but DaTuner has proven to be so powerful, easy to use, and accurate, it\'d be foolish to not use it.\"\n\nhttp://www.androidcentral.com/android-app-review-tuner-datuner-pro\n\nDaTuner converts the fundamental frequency to the nearest note and error in cents for quick and easy tuning of your guitar, ukelele, violin, bass, cello, mandolin, piano, harp, saxophone, Ducati timing belt, harmonica, kazoo, you name it.\n\nDaTuner\'s display is easy to read; nearest note and octave is displayed in a giant, easy to read font in the center of the screen, and frequency in hertz plus error in cents is displayed at the bottom of the screen. Sensitivity is auto-adjusted, but can also be adjusted by touch via a bar on the left-hand side of the screen, and the speed/accuracy of the algorithm and the relative frequency (if other than 440Hz) can be adjusted via the configuration menu.\n\nThere is no \"dead zone\" with this tuner app as is the case with many other apps. Instead, the whole display turns green when the incoming frequency is within a configurable range of the target frequency and you can still see small changes in pitch even within the \"in-range\" area. Both the \"in-tune\" range and the colours shown for sharp and flat can be configured in this version. \n\nScreen and filter lock allow you to select the note that you would like to tune to, with filter lock ignoring anything outside of the range of the note you wish to tune, which is useful for tuning in noisy environs.\n\nFeatures:\n1.) No dead zone - screen changes to green when tuning is good.\n2.) Auto-Sensitivity - no configuration required.\n3.) Bright, easy-to-read display.\n4.) Quick, accurate and precise.  < 0.3 cents @ E3 (329.62Hz), <0.1 cents @ C5(1046.5Hz), < 1 cent @ A2 (110Hz)\n5.) Screen lock: Lock to the note you want to tune, even if extremely out of tune and make your way up/down to it.\n6.) Filter lock: Lock and filter to a specific note and filter out everything outside that note\'s range.\n7.) Ad-free!\n8.) Reference frequency adjustment for orchestra tuning.\n9.) Choice of colours for sharp/flat\n\nFeatures in the PRO version [not in this free version]\n10.) [PRO] Transposition.\n11.) [PRO] Temperaments. [PRO] Emulated strobe tuner display\n14.) [PRO] Digital readout of error in cents\n15.) [PRO] Pitch pipe (triangle, sine, sawtooth, square)\n16.) [PRO] Pitch pipe auto mode (no touch!)\n17.) [PRO] Accelerated tuning algorithm.\n18.) [PRO] Sample rate range 8kHz - 48kHz.\n\nI have tried my best to eliminate bugs from this software, and I apologize in advance for any problems you might find.   ExtendedInfo {
    description: "BubbleUPnP is a full featured UPnP/DLNA Control Point,  UPnP Media Renderer and UPnP Media Server. Play easily your music, videos and images on your phone and devices on your network (DLNA TVs, XBMC, WMP, ...), from your external UPnP Media Servers. Play your phone/tablet media to those devices.\nBrowse and play your local phone/tablet media from other devices (PS3, ...). \nBubbleUPnP can also be used as a standalone music player, even without any network connection.\n\nFree version has some limitations (see end of this description) that can be removed by purchasing the BubbleUPnP License app.\n\nOptional Internet Streaming:\nMore than just regular LAN streaming, BubbleUPnP offer the unique feature to stream efficiently your media via the Internet over a mobile or WiFi connection. Internet streaming requires installing server software \"BubbleUPnP Server\" running on Windows, MacOS X, Linux or a NAS (it is not required for regular LAN streaming, see NOTE below). To learn more about BubbleUPnP Server and Internet streaming visit http://www.bubblesoftapps.com/bubbleupnpserver\n\nNOTE: YOU DO NOT NEED TO INSTALL BUBBLEUPNP SERVER FOR REGULAR UPNP/DLNA LAN STREAMING.\n\nPlease submit any feedback and issues on http://forum.xda-developers.com/showthread.php?t=1118891. For issues you can contact me directly as there is no way I can contact you with Market comments.\n\nFeatures:\n\n- Tablet, ICS, GoogleTV support, landscape mode\n- stream music and videos from your UPnP/DLNA Media Server (Twonky, Asset UPnP, any NAS with UPnP, ...) to your Android device.\n- Codecs supported for audio local playback: with system decoders: MP3, AAC (without DRM), WMA, Ogg Vorbis. With app\'s own decoders: WAV, FLAC, ALAC, LPCM. Samplerates > 48Khz and 24 bits supported for FLAC, WAV. \n- Video playback is delegated to an external app (VPlayer, MoboPlayer, DICE Player,...)\n- stream music/videos from your UPnP/DLNA Media Server to your UPnP renderers with regular playback controls (play, pause, seek, volume, ...). \n- UPnP Media Server (Android 2.2+): play your local phone/tablet media to other devices or to your Android device (standalone media player). Browse and play your local phone/tablet media from other devices (PS3, WMP, ...). Able to browse the SD Card.\n- UPnP renderer: control media playback of your android device from another UPnP Control point\n- Internet streaming/downloading over a mobile or WiFi connection with BubbleUPnP Server\n- UPnP tethering with BubbleUPnP Server (makes Media Servers from a LAN visible on another LAN)\n- Download tracks, full albums and videos from your Media Server to your android device (with covers if available), to make them available in your favorite Android music and media player\n- can play additional media to renderer through 3rd party apps: podcasts (Pocket Casts), shoutcast radio (XiiaLive), youtube,dailymotion,... (semperVidLinks)\n- Gallery-like image viewer\n- Mute / Repeat / Shuffle\n- Editable playlist to queue tracks for playback\n- Fully editable saved playlists\n- Shuffle Playlist\n- Shuffle Library (shuffle tracks from your entire Media Server)\n- Scrobbling support\n- Sleep Timer\n- Display album art\n- Display artist info from Last.fm (requires Last.fm app)\n- Powerful UPnP Search. Search for tracks, albums, artists and videos (exact support depends on Media Server)\n- Bookmarks. Access quickly albums and folders\n- Random track list generation. Discover forgotten gems in your Library\n- Multiple selection. swipe many items to apply a common operation\n\n\nBubbleUPnP free version limitations:\n\n- ads\n- Internet streaming with BubbleUPnP Server is limited to 30 minutes per app launch\n- Playlist and Library Shuffle are limited to 16 tracks\n- downloads limited to batches of maximum 40 tracks\n- the local renderer is remotely controllable by external Control Points for 30 mins per app launch\n- the local Media Server is not browsable by filesystem (SD Card)\n- playing media from external apps is limited to 3 plays per app launch"

This app is being provided completely free of charge, with no adverts, for your benefit.  See the following text for a description of the available sound visualization modes.\n.\nUnique features help you work out the chords to new tunes, visualize the pitch and consistency of the human voice, violin or other instrument, or answer the questions \"what notes am I humming\", \"what are those chords\", \"am I hitting all the notes in tune\", \"is my vibrato consistent\" etc. Select from a list of common instrument tunings or quickly create and manage your own using the built-in tuning editor.\n\nEight separate visualization modes:\n\n1) Instrument: Combination radial strobe and string/note indicators for easy instrument tuning.  Includes a database of common tunings for Guitar, Violin/Fiddle, Mandolin, Ukulele, Banjo, Bouzouki and Pedal Steel, plus a built-in editor for up to 100 user-defined instrument tunings.\n\n2) Dial & Strobe: Combination dial tuner and innovative linear strobe for rapid and extremely accurate hands-free instrument tuning (this linear strobe is a genuine implementation of the strobe-tuner concept, not a decorative imitation).\n\n3) Chromatic Dials: 12-way simultaneous display, with a separate dial tuner for each of the 12 notes in the chromatic scale, to visualize multiple voiced notes or chords.\n\n4) Chromatic Tiles: 12-way simultaneous display of the notes in the chromatic scale, optimized for the visualization of rapid note/pitch changes (e.g. vibrato, arpeggio, portamento, glissando etc).\n\n5) Spectrogram: Scrolling display of live sound analysis, showing the polyphonic perceived pitch of a wide range of sound types (including human voices and singing).\n\n6) Chords: Grid-based estimation display of common chord types (maj/min, maj7/min7, dom7/dim7), ideal for quickly determining the \'strum along\' chords for a tune where the chords are reasonably clear.\n\n7) Partials: A multi-way strobe and waveform display, showing individual note partials along with full note timbre for detailed analysis of sound characteristics.\n\n8) BigStrobe: A large, single strobe display, optimized for small screen devices.\n\nThese visualization modes are easily accessed by swiping the screen left/right or by pressing & holding the tuner display to get a pop-up view selection menu.  User-selectable options are accessed via the MENU button or the pop-up view selection menu and include support for custom temperaments.\n\nPlease rate or review, check for updates regularly and email pitchlabapp@gmail.com to report issues for quick resolution.\n\nExample instrument tunings:\n\nGuitar, Standard\nGuitar, Drop D\nGuitar, Open D\nGuitar, Open G\nGuitar, Open A\nGuitar, Lute\nGuitar, Irish\n\nBass Guitar, (4 String), Standard\nBass Guitar, (5 String), Low B\nBass Guitar, (5 String), Low E\nBass Guitar, (6 String), Standard\n\nViolin: Standard, Tenor\n\nViola: Standard\n\t\t\t\nFiddle: Standard, Cajun, Open G, Sawmill, Gee-dad, Open D, High bass, Cross tuning, Calico\n\nMandolin: Standard, Octave\n\nUkulele: Standard, D6/Soprano, Tenor, Baritone, Bass\n\nBanjo (5 string): Standard/Open G, C tuning, Double C, Sawmill, Open D, Guitar, Willie Moore, Doc Bog\'s D, Cumberland Gap, G Minor, Open C\n\nBanjo: Plectrum, Tenor Standard, Tenor Irish, Long neck\n\nBouzouki: 8 string, 6 string\n\nPedal Steel: Standard/E9th, C6th, A7th, C Diatonic"
